LU-0000 llapi: add SOM mirror layout support

Implement userspace API for creating SOM mirror
layouts and validating them. SOM (Size-on-MDS)
mirrors are metadata-only mirrors that track file
size without storing actual data.

Changes include:

1. Add "som" to lov_pattern_names[] array for
   display purposes

2. Block LCME_FL_SOM in llapi_layout_comp_flags_set()
   - users must use dedicated API

3. Add llapi_layout_comp_add_som() API to create SOM
   mirror components with zero stripes and 0-to-EOF
   extent

4. Block stripe count/size setting on SOM components
   in llapi_layout_stripe_count_set() and
   layout_stripe_size_set()

5. Skip SOM mirrors in llapi_mirror_find() as they
   have no data to sync

6. Add SOM layout sanity validation:
   - SOM component must span from 0 to EOF
   - Only one SOM mirror allowed per file
   - SOM must have zero stripes
   - SOM components cannot have prefer flags

7. Add LSE_SOM_* error codes and messages

This phase focuses only on layout creation and
validation - no resync support yet.

